INSERT Items(ID,Titel,Categorie,Postcode,Locatie,Land,Verkoper,Prijs,Valuta,Conditie,Thumbnail,Beschrijving) VALUES (191380017486,'24 Holy Roman Empire Prince-Elector or Emperors Waterslide Transfers 15mm/28mm',123860,'E79BZ','Verenigd Koninkrijk','GB','dyson690','4.25','GBP','Nieuw','img191380017486.jpg','<p><strong><font face="Times">6 x 4 each of the Prince-Electors Coats of Arms [24 transfers in all] or 24 Holy Roman Empire Double Headed Eagle transfers</font></strong></p><p><strong><font face="Times">Available in two different sizes [Please ensure you state which size and type you want]</font></strong><br><br>You are purchasing six identical waterslide transfer sets [four in each set] for each of the six German Prince-Electors of the Holy Roman Empire.</p><p>Each transfer is no higher than 10mm or no wider than 9mm so they are suitable to be used on 15mm and 28mm scale warwagons, pavise&nbsp;or tents.</p><p>Also available are water slide transfers of the double headed eagle as&nbsp;used for the symbol of the Holy Roman Emperor.<br><br>The tranfers are&nbsp;also availble in a smaller size which are perfect for decorating the fronts of tabards or as shield blazons rather that trying to fit the many different makes of figures shields.</p><p>Please ensure that you specify which size and version of transfers you are buying.</p><p>They are:<br><br>Mainz - red with white wheel symbol<br><br>Koln - white with black cross<br><br>Trier - white with red cross<br><br>Palatinate - yellow lion quarters with the arms of Bavaria<br><br>Saxony - black/white partioned with Saxon green and yellow<br><br>Brandenburg - white with red eagle<br><br>They are designed to be used on the sides of German warwagons but may be suitable for other uses such as affixing to standards, on civic warwagons or as decorations to tents.<br><br>They may well do for other cities and nations as heraldry was often duplicated by other countries.<br><br>The pictures uploaded show them affixed to the sides of my own German warwagons and tents and are for illustrative purposes and these are not included in the sale.<br><br>You are ONLY buying the transfers, nothing else.<br><br>To apply the transfers follow the instructions below:<br><br>CAREFULLY trim around the outline of each transfer.<br><br>Place the transfer in tepid water for approx 30 seconds.<br><br>Gently lift the transfer whilst still on its backing paper out of the water using tweezers.<br><br>Place the transfer near to its final position and gently slide out the paper backing from underneather the transfer.<br><br>Position the transfer in to its final position and gently pat is down using some kitchen roll or similar.<br><br>Once you have done this apply gentle pressure to ensure any air bubbles are pushed out and so it adheres to any contours or folds you may have underneath.<br><br>Leave the transfer to dry fully for about 60 minutes and then apply a protective coat of varnish.</p>')
